Here's the program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Text.Json.Serialization.Metadata;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    TypeInfoResolver = new DefaultJsonTypeInfoResolver()
};

// 1) Strongly-typed metadata — cast GetTypeInfo(Type) to JsonTypeInfo<T>
JsonTypeInfo<int[]> arrayInfo = (JsonTypeInfo<int[]>)options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(int[]));
Console.WriteLine($"Typed metadata for int[]: Kind={arrayInfo.Kind}");

// 2) Probe without throwing — TryGetTypeInfo returns false instead of throwing
if (options.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(string), out JsonTypeInfo? stringInfo))
    Console.WriteLine($"string metadata found: Kind={stringInfo.Kind}");
else
    Console.WriteLine("string metadata NOT available");

// Demonstrate probe failure: no resolver configured
var empty = new JsonSerializerOptions { TypeInfoResolver = null };
if (empty.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(string), out _))
    Console.WriteLine("Unexpected");
else
    Console.WriteLine("Probe correctly returned false — no resolver configured");
```

**Key APIs:**

| Goal | API |
|------|-----|
| Strongly-typed info | `(JsonTypeInfo<T>)options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(T))` |
| Check without throwing | `options.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(T), out JsonTypeInfo? info)` — returns `false` if no resolver can supply metadata |

`TryGetTypeInfo` (added in .NET 9) is the "probe" you want — no try/catch needed.
